<div class="container">
    <h1>Google Shopping Merchant Sample</h1>

    {{#if isLoggedIn}}
        <h3><strong>Logged in as:</strong> {{user.email}}</h3>


        <div class="user-info">
            <p>This action should be triggered once. At this point probably you configured a new project at https://console.cloud.google.com, added oauth login and enabled the Merchant API</p>
            <p>But there is one more step in order to be able to pull information from https://merchants.google.com/ using this app and is to add yourself to the project as developer. This button does the trick.</p>
            <p>For more details access to https://developers.google.com/merchant/api/guides/quickstart#register_your_google_cloud_project</p>

            {{#if developerRegistration}}
                <div class="user-info">
                    <h3>Developer Registration Status</h3>
                    <p><strong>Developer Email:</strong> {{developerRegistration.developerEmail}}</p>
                    <p><strong>Registration Name:</strong> {{developerRegistration.name}}</p>
                    <p><strong>Status:</strong> <span style="color: green;">Registered</span></p>
                </div>
            {{/if}}


            <div>
                <a href="/auth/register-gcp" class="btn btn-info">Register GCP Project</a>
                <a href="/auth/unregister-gcp" class="btn btn-warning" style="margin-left: 10px;">Unregister GCP Project</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="user-info">
            <a href="/products" class="btn btn-success">View Products</a>
            <a href="/auth/logout" class="btn btn-danger">Logout</a>
        </div>

    {{else}}
        <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 30px;">
            Manage your Google merchant center products from this sample app.
        </p>
        <a href="/auth/google" class="btn">
            Sign in with Google
        </a>
    {{/if}}
</div>